# Files that run on the Linux server must keep LF line endings, whatever the
# machine that edited them uses. A shell script committed with Windows CRLF
# fails on Linux with a confusing "bad interpreter: /usr/bin/env bash^M", and
# systemd/Caddy config is just as picky.
*.sh text eol=lf
deploy/Caddyfile text eol=lf
deploy/*.service text eol=lf
